stry, some to be woven together, some to entangle or fray, others merely to perish and pass away.\n\n- Cecilia Dart-Thornton, Weatherwitch\n|\nTemeraire said, 'It is very nice how many books there are, indeed. And on so many subjects!\n\n- Naomi Novik, His Majesty's Dragon\n|\nFreiheit ist immer die Freiheit des AndersdenkendenFreedom is always, and exclusively, freedom for the one who thinks differently.\n\n- Rosa\n|\nMusic may be the activity that prepared our pre-human ancestors for speech communication and for the very cognitive, representational flexibility necessary to become humans.\n\n- Daniel J. Levitin, This Is Your Brain on Music: The Science of a Human Obsession\n|\nI do not know the answers to life's hard questions, but I do know the One who knows them and that's sufficient...for now.\n\n- Toni\n|\nI don't do regrets. Regrets are pointless. It's too late for regrets. You've already done it, haven't you? You've lived your life. No point wishing you could change it.\n\n- Lemmy\n|\nDon't you think it's better to be extremely happy for a short while, even if you lose it, than to be just okay for your whole life?\n\n- Audrey Niffenegger, The Time Traveler's Wife\n|\nAs a man, casting off worn out garments taketh new ones, so the dweller in the body, entereth into ones that are new.\n\n- Epictetus\n|\ndie daily.hourly, if you'vegot the energy.\n\n- Sherwin Tjia, The World Is a Heartbreaker\n|\nWhere wisdom reigns, there is no conflict between thinking and feeling.\n\n- C.G.\n|\nAction is the pulse of any good story, but the character is the heart. If the action has no consequence to the character, the story loses heart.\n\n- Linda\n|\nFor this reason, it is well said that misfortune is sometimes good for something, for it teaches at the same time that it hurts.\n\n- Christine de Pizan, The Selected Writings\n|\nThe mind is an instrument made up of universal consciousness, egocentric consciousness, societal consciousness, along with education, values, virtues,