ut life.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nHave I not commanded thee? Be strong and of good courage; be not afraid, neither be thou dismayed: for the Lord thy God is with thee withersoever thou goest. Joshua 1:9\n\n- Anonymous, Holy Bible: King James Version\n|\nIf a soul could drown in its own tears, then hers was already dead.\n\n- R.\n|\nLife's greatest tragedy is not that it will someday end, but that most only live to follow directions and sometimes we end up totally lost.\n\n- Alex\n|\nIt is singularity which often makes the worst part of our suffering, as it always does of our conduct.\n\n- Jane\n|\nIn the world there exists no aesthetic plane, not even the aesthetic plane of goodness.\n\n- Clarice Lispector, The Passion According to G.H.\n|\nIgnatius B. Samson, welcome to the Cemetery of Forgotten Books.\n\n- Carlos Ruiz Zafón, The Angel's Game\n|\nWe need to find the light within ourselves, so we can see our true worth.\n\n- Imania\n|\nLike poetry, in times of intense emotion the image returns to me. Like poetry, it stroked my soul and, by turns, lulled and stoked my senses.\n\n- Lisa St. Aubin de Terán, The Palace the Palace\n|\nThose who deny freedom to others, deserve it not for themselves\n\n- Abraham Lincoln, Complete Works - Volume XII\n|\nWithout hope, I wouldn’t even try. Hope lifts me to consider new possibilities so I can stay the course of my desire, no matter what.\n\n- Sharon Weil, ChangeAbility: How Artists, Activists, and Awakeners Navigate Change\n|\nBy chance we met, by choice we become friend\n\n- Millie\n|\nIf food is poetry, is not poetry also food?\n\n- Joyce\n|\nKnowledge does not come to us by details, but in flashes of light from heaven.\n\n- Henry David Thoreau, Walden and Other Writings\n|\nIf you seek happiness, look in the mirror. If you seek love, look elsewhere.\n\n- Thomas\n|\nWriting a book is a blood sport. If it doesn't hurt when you're done, you're probably doing something wrong.\n\n- Kevis\n|\nTo make a deliberate falsification for persona